{
  "texts": [
    "Concepts have a content and an extension.",
    "A concept's content can be thought of as its specification or a description of what the concept is about.",
    "A concept's extension, in contrast, refers to the things that the concept is a about.",
    "For example, the content of the concept 'bachelor' is something like 'an unmarried man' (the concept is 'about' unmarried men), while its extension contains all unmarried men.",
    "While some questions are about content-what is the concept about-others concern extension."
  ]
}